<AbstractNarration>Summary:  This research explores the use of geochemical tracers in a marine gastropod as an indicator of Chilean coastal upwelling.  Mg/Ca will be used to indicate water temperature and Cd/Ca will be used to indicate nutrient content.  Measurements from a series of water samples will be compared to analyses of living shells to test and calibrate the usefulness of the method.</AbstractNarration>
